{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_aPXZoGJ13Z14pWgoTpTRpPM4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→schema: aidd.spec.v1\n     3→\n     4→# Core\n     5→status: draft\n     6→updated_at: \"2026-03-18\"\n     7→ticket: \"TST-001\"\n     8→slug: \"fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\"\n     9→\n    10→owners:\n    11→  product: \"security-team\"\n    12→  tech: \"backend-lead\"\n    13→  qa: \"qa-lead\"\n    14→\n    15→sources:\n    16→  plan: \"aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md\"\n    17→  prd: \"aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md\"\n    18→  tasklist: \"aidd/docs/tasklist/TST-001.md\"\n    19→  interview_log: \"aidd/reports/spec/TST-001.interview.jsonl\"\n    20→\n    21→spec_pack:\n    22→  goal: \"Implement live RBAC enforcement on critical APIs, add auditable role operations trail, and synchronize frontend role guards with session updates via WebSocket\"\n    23→  non_goals:\n    24→    - \"UI for role management (assumes existing admin interface)\"\n    25→    - \"Migration of historical access logs\"\n    26→    - \"Multi-tenant RBAC scope\"\n    27→  constraints:\n    28→    - \"No existing RBAC - build from scratch per interview Q2=D\"\n    29→    - \"WebSocket server must scale with current infrastructure\"\n    30→    - \"Audit logs stored in existing DB (separate table)\"\n    31→    - \"Frontend stack: React + Context/Redux (no changes)\"\n    32→  decisions:\n    33→    - \"Q1: Critical APIs = all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) [Interview: B]\"\n    34→    - \"Q2: Current RBAC = none exists, build from scratch [Interview: D - overrides PRD assumption]\"\n    35→    - \"Q3: Frontend = React + Context/Redux\"\n    36→    - \"Q4: Audit logs = database (separate table)\"\n    37→    - \"Q5: Session sync = WebSocket (push updates)\"\n    38→  risks_top:\n    39→    - \"Performance impact of live RBAC checks → caching strategy with TTL\"\n    40→    - \"Session desync between backend/frontend → websocket/polling mechanism\"\n    41→    - \"Audit log storage growth → retention policy and archiving\"\n    42→  links:\n    43→    spec: \"aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml\"\n    44→\n    45→iteration_decisions:\n    46→  - iteration_id: \"I1\"\n    47→    scope:\n    48→      - api_contract\n    49→      - data_model\n    50→      - tests\n    51→      - roll_out\n    52→      - observability\n    53→    decisions:\n    54→      - \"Backend RBAC middleware with audit logging (Phase 1)\"\n    55→      - \"WebSocket push notifications infrastructure (Phase 2)\"\n    56→      - \"Frontend WebSocket integration + Redux state sync (Phase 3)\"\n    57→      - \"Q1: Critical APIs = all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) [Interview: B]\"\n    58→      - \"Q2: No existing RBAC - build from scratch [Interview: D]\"\n    59→    open_questions: []\n    60→\n    61→platforms:\n    62→  frontend:\n    63→    enabled: true\n    64→    stack_hint: \"React + Context/Redux\"\n    65→  backend:\n    66→    enabled: true\n    67→    stack_hint: \"Build from scratch - no existing RBAC (per interview Q2=D)\"\n    68→  mobile:\n    69→    enabled: false\n    70→    stack_hint: \"\"\n    71→\n    72→user_flows:\n    73→  - id: \"flow.admin-change-role\"\n    74→    actors: [\"admin\", \"target_user\"]\n    75→    entrypoints: [\"PUT /api/users/{id}/role\"]\n    76→    steps:\n    77→      - \"Admin calls API to change user role\"\n    78→      - \"RBAC middleware checks admin permissions\"\n    79→      - \"Role updated in DB, operation logged to audit_log\"\n    80→      - \"WebSocket push notification sent to target user\"\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"tool_9IR3nXM2Nf0L1wjiagWF1fMD","ses