{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_9IR3nXM2Nf0L1wjiagWF1fMD","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Status:** COMPLETE\n\n**Work item key:** TST-001\n\n**Artifacts updated:**\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml` - Updated with interview answers\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/reports/spec/TST-001.interview.jsonl` - Created interview log\n\n**Changes made to spec.yaml:**\n1. **Status changed:** `ready` → `draft` (due to significant architectural change from interview)\n2. **Q1 decision updated:** \"Critical APIs = all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) [Interview: B]\"\n3. **Q2 decision updated:** \"Current RBAC = none exists, build from scratch [Interview: D - overrides PRD assumption]\"\n4. **Constraints updated:** Changed from \"Integrate with existing JWT-claims middleware\" to \"No existing RBAC - build from scratch per interview Q2=D\"\n5. **Backend stack hint updated:** Reflects the need to build from scratch\n6. **Open questions:** Cleared blocker questions since Q2=D resolves the architecture approach\n7. **Iteration decisions:** Added interview answers to the I1 iteration\n\n**Key finding from interview:**\n- Q2=D indicates **no existing RBAC** in the codebase, which is a significant change from the PRD assumption (Q2=B - custom JWT-claims middleware). This means the implementation needs to build RBAC from scratch rather than extending existing middleware.\n\n**Tests:** N/A (spec documentation update)\n\n**Blockers/Handoff:** None\n\n**Next actions:**\n- The spec status is `draft` due to the architectural change (no existing RBAC). The planner should review and may need to update the implementation plan to reflect building RBAC from scratch rather than extending existing JWT middleware.\n- Once reviewed, status can be changed back to `ready` for implementation.\n\n**AIDD:READ_LOG